==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermic
<hw>Ther"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ heat.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to heat; due to heat; thermal; <as>as,
<ex>thermic</ex> lines</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Thermic balance</b></col>. <cd>See
<er>Bolometer</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Thermic fever</b></col>
<fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>the condition of fever produced by sunstroke. See
<er>Sunstroke</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Thermic weight</b></col>.
<fld>(Mech.)</fld> <cd>Same as <cref>Heat weight</cref>, under
<er>Heat</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermidor</ent>⟦br⟧
